docs.abstract: Irish political party Sinn Fein, once encumbered by its close association with Irish Republican Army, evolves into leading representative of mainstream, leftist opposition; party, positioned by leader Gerry Adams as populist, anti-austerity alternative to main center right, is poised to make significant gains in upcoming Parliamentary elections.
